Privacy Policy for Johnny Wicked Survivors

This Privacy Policy explains how EmergencyDefiant5381 ("we," "us," or "our") handles information when you use the mobile or web game Johnny Wicked Survivors (the "Game").

1. Information We Collect

We are committed to collecting only the data necessary to provide and improve the Game's core function: the High Score leaderboard.

    Game Performance Data: We collect non-personal data related to your in-game performance, which includes: Survival Time, Final Score, and Achieved Level.

    Player Identifier: We collect an anonymous or pseudo-anonymous identifier (such as a device ID, a session ID, or a game-specific username/ID) that is used only to link your high scores to a specific entry on the public leaderboard.

2. How We Use the Information

The information collected is used exclusively for the following purposes:

    Leaderboard Functionality: To save your scores and display them publicly on the in-game high score leaderboard.

    Game Improvement: To analyze overall game difficulty and player progression to inform future updates.

    Preventing Cheating: To monitor and verify the integrity of high scores and the ranking system.

3. Data Storage and Third-Party Service

    Firebase: We use Google Firebase to securely store and manage the high score data. Their services are governed by the Google Privacy Policy.

    Data Location: Data stored by Firebase may be processed in the United States or other countries where Google or its service providers maintain facilities.

4. Public Display of Information

You acknowledge that the purpose of the High Score system is to share performance data. Therefore:

    Your Game Performance Data (Score, Time, Level) will be publicly visible on the in-game leaderboard.

    Your associated Player Identifier (e.g., your chosen in-game name or ID) will be publicly displayed next to your score.

5. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect. By playing the Game, you accept the inherent risks of data transmission.

6. Children's Privacy

The Game is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy. Your continued use of the Game after the changes are posted means you accept those changes.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us via a private message on Reddit to EmergencyDefiant5381.
